{"questionId":"9069283","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>When heated in air, magnesium ribbon reacts with oxygen to form magnesium oxide.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The reaction in (a)(i) was carried out in a crucible with a lid and the following data was recorded:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Mass of crucible and lid = 47.372 ±0.001 g</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Mass of crucible, lid and magnesium ribbon before heating = 53.726 ±0.001 g</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Mass of crucible, lid and product after heating = 56.941 ±0.001 g</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the amount of magnesium, in mol, that was used.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⟨</mo><mo>⟨</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>53</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>726</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>47</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>372</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>244</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>31</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>354</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>24</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>31</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>mol</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>⟩</mo><mo>⟩</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2614</mn><mo> </mo><mo>«</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo>»</mo><mo>✔</mo></math></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069283","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ1.b(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the amount of magnesium, in mol, that was used.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.2 The mole concept","Core","Topic 1: Stoichi